The President spoke with Japanese Prime Minister Naoto Kan to discuss the ongoing relief efforts in Japan, particularly the emergency at the Fukushima nuclear plant. The President conveyed condolences for the loss of life and suffering in Northeastern Japan and reiterated the US's commitment to support Japan in overcoming the effects of the earthquake and tsunami. The President briefed the Prime Minister on additional support being provided by the US, including specialized military assets with expertise in nuclear response. They also discussed the welfare and safety of American citizens in Japan. Prime Minister Kan updated the President on Japanese actions to contain the nuclear emergency and expressed appreciation for the support from the US. The two leaders agreed to continue close cooperation and to remain in touch during this challenging period. The President promised that the US will always stand by Japan and expressed confidence in Japan's ability to recover from the disaster.